claim.claim-text:
6. Method according to any one of claims 1 to 5, characterized in that for the case of an emergency running in which an electronic control of the automatic transmission or of the clutches remains operative, the following steps are carried out: 
diagnose the erroneous state and activate the emergency program (NP) in the electronic transmission control; 
determine the nominal value for the engine torque (T_mot) with reference to the operating parameters for a predetermined time (t_ME) in the electronic transmission control and relay said data to the electronic engine control; 
trigger the engine engagement (ME) in order to reduce the engine torque (T_mot), the intensity of the engine engagement (ME) being function of the relevant operating conditions; 
simultaneous hydraulic activation of the gear clutches for the emergency program shifting operation; 
terminate the engine engagement (ME) according to the predetermined time (t_ME) and change over to the emergency running operation.

7. Method according to any one of claims 1 to 5, characterized in that for in the case of an emergency running in which the electronic control of the automatic transmission or of the clutches is not operative, the following steps are carried out: 
diagnose the erroneous state and -activate the emergency program (NP) in the electronic engine control; 
determine the nominal value for the engine torque (T_mot) with reference to the operating parameters for a predetermined time (t_ME) in the electronic engine control; 
release the engine engagement (ME) in order to reduce the engine torque (T_mot), the intensity of the engine engagement (ME) being function of the relevant operating conditions; 
a simultaneous hydraulic activation of the gear clutches for the emergency program shifting operation; 
terminate the engine engagement (ME) according to the predetermined time (t_ME) and 
change over to the emergency running operation.
